race.comment: BEST OF THE BEST (6) resumes for his second campaign. He was a very smart winner on debut at Sale which saw the camp test the waters in the G3 Mcneil Stakes, battling home there behind some talented types. He's won a jumpout leading in and profiles as a horse who can pick his way through a few races this time in. INSAIN HARRY (4) has come back in fine form, winning 2/3 and placing in the other. This is a bit harder but he draws for every chance and can measure up. FLORINA REGION (8) resumes having gone to the paddock a dominant maiden winner at Cranbourne. She's promising and always wary of the lightly raced Begg mare. VOLKANO (11) resumes. He was dominant at Ballarat Synthetic on debut, tackling a Group 3 next time out. There's good ability there, watch the betting. RUSSIAN FRONT (5) is consistent and in the mix again.
